				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lynxsolaris wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">That code is correct, but make sure that the latch is set to the first write otherwise the VRAM address will be set to $C023, not $23C0.</div><br /><br />sorry but what do you mean by "latch"?</div>
<br />
<br /> <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> 
<br />
<br />The latch is a 1-bit PPU value that decides between a high and low byte write. If the latch is not set then the next write to $2006 will be to the upper byte (i.e. $xx00). If it is set then the next write will be to the lower byte (i.e. $00xx).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

